<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1897,2037]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1936,1961]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Identification.</emphasis>
Test oval, concave sides, slightly elevated aborally towards petaliod area. Petals broad, closed, except anterior one, which is open distally. Live specimens reddish brown in color; denuded test white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,2012,2037]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Global maximum size.</emphasis>
Maximum test length 
<specimenCount box="[719,783,2013,2037]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">
